## Disclaimer for the HIPAA reference pack

The `packs/hipaa-reference/` pack ships a starting-point set of PHI patterns
for educational and reference use. It is NOT a HIPAA compliance control,
NOT a certification, NOT legal advice, and NOT a substitute for a HIPAA
Security Rule implementation. The pack's regex patterns were authored by
software engineers, not by a compliance attorney or HIPAA-credentialed
auditor.

Teams using TeamVault to handle PHI-adjacent content must, before relying
on this pack as any layer of defense:

1. Have their own counsel review the regex set against their actual PHI
   shapes and approve (or extend) it for their use case.
2. Execute BAAs with EVERY third party their substrate touches (including
   their git host, embedding-model provider, LLM provider, and any other
   external service).
3. Maintain organizational HIPAA Security Rule controls separately:
   access controls, workforce training, audit-log retention, breach
   response, and periodic risk assessments.
4. Run periodic manual audit beyond automated pattern matching.

The authors and contributors disclaim all liability for PHI leaks via
the shipped patterns, for missed detections, for false negatives, for
incidents arising from reliance on this pack, and for any compliance
deficiency in any organization that enables this pack. The pack is
provided AS-IS, without warranty of any kind.

See [`packs/hipaa-reference/README.md`](packs/hipaa-reference/README.md)
for the operational positioning and the "what you must do if you fork
this" checklist.
